T1  - Inference in Nonlinear Econometric Models with Structural Change
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297408
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 55
IS  - 4
SP  - 615
EP  - 640
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper extends the classical test for structural change in linear regression models (see Chow (1960)) to a wide variety of nonlinear models, estimated by a variety of different procedures. Wald, Lagrange multiplier-like, and likelihood ratio-like test statistics are introduced. The results allow for heterogeneity and temporal dependence of the observations.In the process of developing the above tests, the paper also provides a compact presentation of general unifying results for estimation and testing in nonlinear parametric econometric models.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297408
ER  - 



