JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 55
IS  - 4
SP  - 573
EP  - 592
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Product heterogeneity is introduced into the context of spatial price discrimination. Many of the strong properties of the standard homogeneous goods case (which are attained as a limit case here) are shown to be no longer valid. In particular, the social optimum is no longer sustainable as a market equilibrium unless products are either identical or else very different.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297406
